  "text": "Two complex numbers x, y are called multiplicatively independent if for all k, ∈ Z it holds that x k = y implies k = = 0. We shall use the following version of Cobham's theorem due to Durand [CITATION_1] . Theorem 9. Let α and β be multiplicatively independent Perron numbers. If a sequence w is both α-substitutive and β-substitutive, then w is eventually periodic.",
